==English==

===Etymology===
from the French ''(essence de) [[pétrole]]'' from [[petroleum]], from the Latin ''[[petra]]'' stone, ''[[oleum]]'' oil.

===Pronunciation===
pĕt'rəl, /ˈpetrəl/, /<tt>"petr@l</tt>/

====Homophones====
*[[petrel]]

===Noun===
'''petrol'''

# {{UK}} {{AU}} (''New Zealand'') A fluid consisting of a mixture of refined [[petroleum]] [[hydrocarbon]]s, primarily consisting of [[octane]], and commonly used as a motor [[fuel]].

====Synonyms====
* {{US}} [[gasoline]], [[gas]]

